cards.name: Grill Master Gary
cards.subtitle: Propane is Just a Suggestion
cards.flavorText: McDonald's put microchips in the Big Macs! The Deep State controls the propane prices! But THIS grill? 100% free of government surveillance. Trust me, I saw it on a YouTube video. I told my wife the grill was her fault. She said 'that doesn't even make sense.' I said 'neither does your cooking.' Neither does Big Burger King controlling the weather!

abilities.name: Flame On
abilities.description: Sets everything on fire while ranting about Big Burger King controlling the weather through chemtrails. Including the neighbor's fence. Again. The flames are honest. The conspiracy is hotter.

cards.name: Thermostat Tyrant
cards.subtitle: 68°F or Death
cards.flavorText: The kids tried to touch it! I told them the power company tracks temperature changes through their smart meters. They haven't tried since. The tin foil helps block the 5G mind control. Big HVAC's tracking every adjustment! Smart thermostats are government surveillance portals! I wrapped mine in tinfoil. The protection's questionable. The conspiracy's certain.

abilities.name: Temperature Lockdown
abilities.description: Knows when you touch it. Claims the power company spies through smart meters. Has proof. (It's a YouTube comment section.) From anywhere in the house. The tinfoil helps.

abilities.name: Bill Rage
abilities.description: +500% anger when electric bill arrives. Screams about 'Big Energy' controlling the grid while adjusting it to 68°F exactly. The rage is real. The conspiracy is realer.

cards.name: New Balance Nathan
cards.subtitle: Fashion Fuckery Since 2004
cards.flavorText: Podiatrist said these shoes love me back! Marriage counselor said my dick's divorced! Gucci's got Satan tracker runes in their soles! I wear New Balance. They're honest. Also comfortable.

abilities.name: Maximum Comfort
abilities.description: Has zero f*cks left to give about style. Claims all designer shoes are government tracking devices. Still wears New Balance. It's a statement.

cards.name: Lawn Legend Larry
cards.subtitle: GET OFF MY LAWN
cards.flavorText: I've spent 20 years perfecting this grass! The HOA can suck my ass! These fertilizer brands are fronts for Big Ag trying to control my lawn through chemtrails! My grass is 100% organic conspiracy-free.

abilities.name: Grass Stare
abilities.description: Can detect a single imperfect blade from 100 yards while simultaneously ranting that the neighbors' lawn is a 5G antenna array in disguise.

cards.name: Remote Control Randy
cards.subtitle: Don't Touch The Buttons
cards.flavorText: I'm not asleep, I'm just conducting important REM research! Netflix is brainwashing us with gay frogs! I saw it on Infowars! Now pass me the remote - I need to watch more conspiracy videos.

abilities.name: Button Memory
abilities.description: Knows exactly which button you touched. Claims the remote has a government tracking chip. Still uses it though. Has 47 remotes. All of them are 'compromised.'

cards.name: Handyman Hank
cards.subtitle: Duct Tape & WD-40
cards.flavorText: The plumber wanted $800. I fixed it myself for $15 and a trip to the ER. Home Depot is a front for Area 51 aliens, but their duct tape selection is unmatched. I built a dildo out of WD-40 and determination.

abilities.name: YouTube Master
abilities.description: Watched a 10-minute video. Basically an expert now. Ignores actual experts. Uses duct tape for everything including emotions. Claims YouTube tutorials are government psy-ops.

abilities.name: Hardware Store Wizard
abilities.description: Can navigate Home Depot blindfolded. Claims the store layout changes every week because 'they' don't want us finding the good stuff. Still shops there daily.

cards.name: Bogey Bob
cards.subtitle: It's Not About The Score
cards.flavorText: I'd be better if my back didn't sound like a grenade going off every swing. Nike golf balls are tracking devices. Bill Gates owns the golf courses. I saw it in a Facebook group. Still playing though.

abilities.name: Infinite Mulligans
abilities.description: 'That one didn't count.' - Every single time. Also claims the wind is controlled by Big Golf to sell more balls. Has 47 theories about the course. None of them make sense.

cards.name: Cargo Shorts Carl
cards.subtitle: Pocket Dimension
cards.flavorText: 17 pockets and I still can't find my phone! It's in pocket 4. Always pocket 4. Cargo shorts are a government conspiracy to hide tracking devices! I have 47 pairs. All of them are 'bugged.'

abilities.name: Infinite Storage
abilities.description: Once pulled out a full grill. Nobody knows how. Claims cargo shorts are pocket dimensions created by Area 51. Scientists have studied them. They were confused.

abilities.name: Prepared Dad
abilities.description: Has exactly what you need. Eventually. Claims every pocket holds government surveillance devices. Uses them anyway. The storage is unmatched.

cards.name: Oil Change Oscar
cards.subtitle: 3,000 Miles or Whenever
cards.flavorText: That's not a leak, that's just the car marking its territory! Tesla's turning cars into sex robots! Electric vehicles are government mind control machines! I drive a 1993 Ford F-150. It's honest. Also it leaks.

abilities.name: Engine Whisperer
abilities.description: Can diagnose problems by sound. Sometimes accurate. Claims car manufacturers hide tracking chips in engines. Still drives daily. Has 47 theories about oil changes. All of them involve conspiracies.

cards.name: TPS Report Terry
cards.subtitle: Did You Get The Memo?
cards.flavorText: I'd explain corporate synergy, but I'd have to kill you. Or bore you. Same thing. The TPS reports are a government tracking system. I fill them out with fake data to confuse the deep state. HR thinks I'm just bad at spreadsheets.

abilities.name: Meeting Survivor
abilities.description: Can endure 4-hour meetings about nothing while secretly researching conspiracy theories on his phone under the table. Claims every meeting is a CIA operation.

cards.name: Skateboard Scott
cards.subtitle: The Cool Dad (Confirmed)
cards.flavorText: I was doing kickflips before you were born! Well, attempting them. In my mind. Spotify's algorithms are turning me gay! The playlists are government mind control! I listen anyway. The music's good. The conspiracy's real.

abilities.name: Radical Recall
abilities.description: Remembers every 90s slang word. Uses them wrong anyway. Claims 90s culture was the last honest era before Big Tech took over. Still uses 'rad' unironically.

abilities.name: Hip Injury Risk
abilities.description: 100% chance of throwing back out. Claims injuries are government experiments to test pain tolerance. Has 47 back braces. All of them are 'tracking devices.'

cards.name: Soccer Stan
cards.subtitle: sideline General
cards.flavorText: HUSTLE! HUSTLE! ...Sorry, I'm projecting my unfulfilled dreams. Sports gear is bugged by the FBI! Nike cleats have tracking chips! The refs are Deep State operatives! I coach anyway. The kids need guidance. Also the conspiracies.

abilities.name: Orange Slice Provider
abilities.description: The most important job on the field. Claims orange slices are government mind control snacks. Still provides them. The kids love them. The conspiracy loves them more.

cards.name: Secret Recipe Rick
cards.subtitle: The Secret Is Butter
cards.flavorText: The secret ingredient? Love. And enough butter to kill a horse. Big Food's GMOs made my steaks soft! The secret recipes are government tracking formulas! I cook with real ingredients. They're honest. Also fattening.

abilities.name: Taste Memory
abilities.description: Can recreate any dish. Usually better. Claims restaurant chains put tracking chemicals in their food. Still eats there. Has 47 secret recipes. All of them involve butter.

abilities.name: Kiss The Cook
abilities.description: +50 defense when wearing apron. Claims aprons are government mind control devices. Still wears them. The protection is real. The conspiracy is fake. Or is it?

cards.name: Costco Craig
cards.subtitle: Bulk Buy Boss
cards.flavorText: We don't NEED 47 rolls of toilet paper, but at that price, we'd be stupid not to! Costco is a FEMA camp in disguise! The greeters are government agents! The rollback prices are a trap to track our shopping patterns! Still buys everything there because it's cheap. The value's unmatched. The conspiracy's unmatched-er.

abilities.name: Sample Radar
abilities.description: Can detect free samples from 3 aisles away. Claims samples are laced with tracking chemicals. Eats them anyway. Has 47 theories about Costco. All of them involve federal agents.

abilities.name: Hot Dog Devotion
abilities.description: The $1.50 combo is sacred. Claims it's the last honest transaction in America. Big Hot Dog hasn't gotten to Costco yet. Still just $1.50. It's a miracle. DO NOT QUESTION IT.

cards.name: Christmas Clark
cards.subtitle: Decorate Or Die
cards.flavorText: The neighbors said my lights were 'too bright!' I added 5,000 more. They've since moved. Hallmark movies brainwash my kids! Christmas lights are government tracking devices! Santa's a CIA operative! I put up 47,000 lights. The power bill is astronomical. But the message is clear: I'm watching them watch me.

abilities.name: Ladder Courage
abilities.description: No roof is too high. No hospital visit too expensive. Claims extension cords are government tracking wires. Still uses 47 of them. The fire department knows me by name.

abilities.name: Extension Cord Master
abilities.description: Can daisy-chain 47 power strips. Fire department is on speed dial. Claims every cord sends data to Big Electric. Still plugs them all in. The neighbors' lights flicker. It's a feature, not a bug.

cards.name: The Ultimate Dad
cards.subtitle: Hi Hungry, I'm Dad
cards.flavorText: I brought you into this world, and I'll take you out! After I finish this burger. The burger industry is a conspiracy to make us fat and docile. This burger? 100% grass-fed, government-free, chemtrail-resistant beef. Eat up.

abilities.name: Dad Joke Mastery
abilities.description: Every joke lands. The groans are deafening. Claims dad jokes are the last bastion of free speech before the woke mob cancels everything. Has 47 jokes ready at all times.

abilities.name: Universal Remote
abilities.description: Controls everything. Even you. Has 47 remotes because 'they' want us dependent on smart home technology. Still uses all of them. The contradiction is beautiful.

abilities.name: Infinite Wisdom
abilities.description: Actually knows everything (confirmed by him). All knowledge comes from YouTube comment sections and Facebook groups. It's basically a PhD. Has 47 conspiracy theories about everything.

cards.name: WiFi Wizard Walter
cards.subtitle: Have You Tried Turning It Off?
cards.flavorText: I changed the password again! Read the sticky note on the fridge. No, the other one. The WiFi router is sending our data to the Chinese government! That's why I reboot it 47 times a day. Can't be too careful. Big Router's tracking every connection! WiFi's a government surveillance portal! I still use it. The convenience is unmatched. The conspiracy is unmatched-er.

abilities.name: Router Reboot
abilities.description: Fixes 90% of problems. The other 10%? More rebooting. Claims each reboot resets the government tracking chips. Has 47 sticky notes with passwords on the fridge. The reboots are frequent. The paranoia is constant.

cards.name: Smoker Steve
cards.subtitle: Low & Slow Legend
cards.flavorText: 12 hours? That's just getting started! The meat isn't done until I say it's done. Or until tomorrow. Ronald McFuckface controls the weather through chemtrails! But THIS smoker? 100% free of government surveillance. The smoke is honest. The conspiracy is real.

abilities.name: Smoke Ring Summoner
abilities.description: Perfect smoke ring. Every. Single. Time. Claims smoke rings are signals to aliens. Still makes perfect ones. The neighbors are impressed. The government is watching.

abilities.name: Patience of a Saint
abilities.description: Will wait 18 hours for perfect brisket. Will not wait 5 minutes for you. Claims patience is a lost art destroyed by Big Fast Food. Still practices it daily. Has 47 theories about brisket. All of them involve conspiracies.

cards.name: Minivan Mike
cards.subtitle: Swagger Wagon Commander
cards.flavorText: It's not a minivan, it's a mobile command center with built-in goldfish cracker storage! Tesla's turning cars into sex robots! Minivans are the last honest vehicles before Big Electric took over! I drive a 2004 Odyssey. It's perfect. Also it has 47 cup holders.

abilities.name: Snack Compartment
abilities.description: Emergency rations for any crisis (all 5 flavors). Claims snack companies put tracking chips in goldfish crackers. Still buys them in bulk. The storage is unmatched. The conspiracy is delicious.

cards.name: Recliner Randy
cards.subtitle: Horizontal Life Evaluation
cards.flavorText: This isn't sleeping. This is strategic consciousness pause! Netflix is brainwashing us with gay frogs! Infowars told me so! I nap for 12 hours daily. It's research. The REM cycles are coded messages. I'm decoding them.

abilities.name: Power Nap
abilities.description: 20 minutes. Fully recharged. Still tired. Claims power naps reset government mind control chips. Still tired anyway. Has 47 theories about sleep. All of them involve aliens.

abilities.name: Snore Denial
abilities.description: Claims to never snore. Recording suggests otherwise. Has proof he doesn't snore. (It's a YouTube video that proves he does.) The denial is real. The snoring is louder.

cards.name: Fertilizer Fred
cards.subtitle: Grass Growth Guru
cards.flavorText: The secret is in the nitrogen-phosphorus-potassium ratio! Trust me, I have a degree. From YouTube. Scotts Miracle-Gro is a Bilderberg Group conspiracy! Fertilizer companies spike turf with mind control chemicals! I mix my own. It's honest. Also it smells worse.

abilities.name: Dandelion Destroyer
abilities.description: Can spot a weed from a moving vehicle. Claims dandelions are government plants to track lawn owners. Still pulls them. Has 47 theories about weeds. All of them involve the Deep State.

cards.name: LinkedIn Larry
cards.subtitle: Humble Brag Master
cards.flavorText: Excited to announce that I'm excited to announce that I'm excited to announce that I'm exhausted! LinkedIn's a CIA recruitment platform! Every humble brag sends data to the Deep State! I post daily anyway. It's networking. Also it's surveillance.

abilities.name: Infinite Humble Brag
abilities.description: Every post is secretly an achievement. Claims LinkedIn tracks our career moves to control the job market. Still uses it. Has 47 connections. All of them are 'compromised.'

cards.name: Band Dad Brad
cards.subtitle: Almost Got Signed
cards.flavorText: We almost got signed. ALMOST. The record label just 'didn't get our vision.' 20 years ago. Big Music's controlling the industry through Spotify algorithms! Record labels are government fronts for mind control! I still play. The garage is my stage. The neighbors are my unwilling audience.

abilities.name: Air Guitar God
abilities.description: Can shred invisible strings like nobody's business. Claims the music industry is a Deep State conspiracy. Still plays air guitar daily. Has 47 theories about why we didn't get signed. All of them involve the Illuminati.

cards.name: Classic Car Craig
cards.subtitle: It's A Classic, Not A Clunker
cards.flavorText: They don't make 'em like they used to! Thank God. These things are death traps. But she's beautiful. Car manufacturers hide tracking chips in classic cars! Old vehicles are government surveillance platforms! I still drive mine. The style's unmatched. The conspiracy's unmatched-er.

abilities.name: Part Archaeologist
abilities.description: Can find discontinued parts from the Cold War era. Claims old car parts are government tracking devices. Still uses them. Has 47 theories about why they stopped making them. All of them involve aliens.

abilities.name: Weekend Warrior
abilities.description: Has been 'almost done' for 7 years. Trust me though. Claims the restoration's delayed by government interference. Still working on it. The neighbors are concerned. The conspiracy is eternal.

cards.name: Breakfast King Keith
cards.subtitle: Pancake Perfectionist
cards.flavorText: Saturday morning pancakes are non-negotiable! Burn them and you're disowned. Big Breakfast's trying to control my morning routine through IHOP conspiracies! I make my own pancakes. They're honest. Also they're perfect.

abilities.name: Flip Master
abilities.description: Never dropped a pancake. The walls disagree. Claims pancake mix is a government tracking powder. Still uses it. Has perfected the flip. The walls are covered in batter. It's art.

cards.name: Weber Genesis Grill
cards.subtitle: The Sacred Flame
cards.flavorText: Four burners of pure cock-power! Side burner for fuckin' beans. I love this grill more than I love my kids. Weber's the only grill company not controlled by Big Gas! The neighbors are jealous. The fence is on fire. It's perfect.

abilities.name: Perfect Heat Distribution
abilities.description: No hot spots, just pure fire everywhere. Neighbors are jealous. Claims Weber grills are the last honest grills before Big Gas took over. Still uses propane. The contradiction is real.

cards.name: La-Z-Boy Throne
cards.subtitle: Seat of Power
cards.flavorText: Built-in cup holders. Heated massage. This is the endgame. This is what we work for. La-Z-Boy's the only chair company not controlled by Big Furniture! Every recline is an act of rebellion against corporate America! I've fallen asleep in this chair 47 times this week. It's perfect.

abilities.name: Infinite Recline
abilities.description: Adjusts to any position. Even ones that shouldn't exist. Claims recliners are government mind control devices. Still sits in it 12 hours a day. Has achieved maximum recline. The neighbors are concerned.

cards.name: Craftsman Toolbox
cards.subtitle: Inherited From Grandpa
cards.flavorText: Every tool has a story. Most involve grandpa swearing. A lot. Craftsman tools are the only tools not controlled by Big Hardware! Grandpa left me this toolbox. It's full of stories and government tracking chips. I use them anyway. The tools work. The conspiracy is bonus.

abilities.name: Right Tool, Right Job
abilities.description: Has exactly what you need. If you can find it. Claims every tool in the box is a government surveillance device. Still uses them. Has 47 tools. Can only find 3. The other 44 are in a parallel dimension.

cards.name: Cargo Shorts of Holding
cards.subtitle: Pocket Dimension
cards.flavorText: 17 pockets. Each one a mystery. Still can't find my keys though. Cargo shorts are government tracking devices disguised as fashion! Every pocket is a surveillance portal! I wear them anyway. The storage is unmatched. The conspiracy is real.

abilities.name: Defies Physics
abilities.description: Scientists have studied them. They were confused. Claims cargo shorts are pocket dimensions created by Area 51 aliens. Can store infinite items. Still can't find keys. They're in pocket 4. Always pocket 4.

cards.name: The Thermostat
cards.subtitle: Source of Marital Discord
cards.flavorText: He who controls the thermostat, controls the household! The negotiations never end. Big HVAC's tracking every temperature change through smart thermostats! This thermostat? 100% analog, conspiracy-free, government-surveillance-resistant! The wife still changes it. She's compromised.

abilities.name: Temperature Lock
abilities.description: Biometric security. Only the worthy may adjust. Claims smart thermostats are government tracking devices. Still has one. Has wrapped it in tinfoil. The tinfoil helps. Probably.

abilities.name: Bill Display
abilities.description: Shows real-time energy cost. Wife still changes it. Claims the energy company tracks temperature changes to control our minds. Still adjusts it anyway. The bill is high. The conspiracy is higher.

cards.name: Propane Paul
cards.subtitle: Tank Tender
cards.flavorText: Taste the meat, not the heat! Also, ignore the gas smell. That's normal. Probably. Propane companies are fronts for the Illuminati! Big Gas controls prices through chemtrail board meetings! I use propane anyway. It's convenient. The conspiracy is a bonus.

abilities.name: Tank Gauge Intuition
abilities.description: Knows exactly how many burgers remain. To the decimal. Claims propane tanks have government tracking chips. Still uses them. Has 47 tanks. All of them are 'compromised.'

cards.name: YouTube Tutorial Tom
cards.subtitle: 10 Minutes To Expert
cards.flavorText: I watched a 10-minute video. I'm basically a professional now. What could go wrong? YouTube tutorials are government psy-ops! Home Depot hides Area 51 tech in aisle 5! I still watch them. The knowledge is real. The conspiracy is bonus.

abilities.name: Video Pause Master
abilities.description: Can follow tutorials perfectly. Results may vary. Claims YouTube is a Deep State mind control platform. Still uses it daily. Has 47 subscriptions. All of them are 'compromised.'

cards.name: Country Club Chad
cards.subtitle: Back Nine Boss
cards.flavorText: It's not about winning, it's about the business deals on the back nine! And the drinking. Mostly the drinking. Nike golf balls have Bill Gates spyware! The country club's a CIA front for networking mind control! I still play. The deals are real. The conspiracy is realer.

abilities.name: Networking Drive
abilities.description: Every round is a business opportunity. Somehow. Claims golf courses are government surveillance platforms. Still plays weekly. Has 47 theories about the club. All of them involve federal agents.

cards.name: Little League Lou
cards.subtitle: Dugout Dynamo
cards.flavorText: Keep your eye on the ball! No, THE OTHER BALL! You know what, just don't quit. Sports gear is bugged by the FBI! Nike cleats have tracking chips! The refs are Deep State operatives! I coach anyway. The kids need encouragement. Also the conspiracies.

abilities.name: Encouragement Aura
abilities.description: 'Good job!' is his battle cry. Even when you suck. Claims every game is fixed by the Illuminati. Still coaches daily. Has 47 theories about sports. All of them are wrong but entertaining.

cards.name: Riding Mower Rex
cards.subtitle: Lawn Cavalry
cards.flavorText: Zero-turn radius. Maximum dad satisfaction! The neighbors are both impressed and concerned. John Deere's got spy blades in every mower! Lawn mowers are government tracking devices! I still use mine. The stripes are perfect. The conspiracy is real.

abilities.name: Stripe Perfection
abilities.description: Creates MLB-quality lawn patterns. The HOA is confused. Claims mower manufacturers hide tracking chips in blades. Still mows weekly. Has 47 theories about grass. All of them involve the Deep State.

abilities.name: Cup Holder Tech
abilities.description: Never spills a beverage. Even at full speed. Claims cup holders are government listening devices. Still uses them. The drinks stay cold. The conspiracy stays hot.

cards.name: World's Best Dad Mug
cards.subtitle: Unverified but Emotional
cards.flavorText: Scientifically unverified, emotionally accurate! Don't question it. Big Mug's trying to control my morning routine through coffee conspiracies! This mug's the only one not tracked by Starbucks! The coffee tastes better. The conspiracy tastes real.

abilities.name: Morning Confidence
abilities.description: Coffee tastes 47% better from this mug. Confirmed. Claims coffee companies put mind control chemicals in every cup. Still drinks it daily. Has 47 mugs. All of them say 'World's Best Dad.' None of them are verified.

cards.name: Oakley Wraparounds
cards.subtitle: Tactical Eye Protection
cards.flavorText: Polarized lenses for maximum fish-spotting! Also hides the eye rolls from your wife. Oakley's got spy lenses that track my every gaze! Sunglasses are government surveillance devices! I still wear them. The glare protection is real. The conspiracy is realer.

abilities.name: Glare Immunity
abilities.description: Never squints. Even directly at the sun. Claims sunglasses are government tracking devices. Still wears them. Has 47 pairs. All of them are 'compromised.' The sun doesn't care.

cards.name: Cell Phone Holster
cards.subtitle: Quick Draw
cards.flavorText: Quick draw texting! Hands-free hip storage! The kids are embarrassed. Good. Cell phone holsters are government tracking devices! Big Tech's monitoring every hip movement! I still use it. The convenience is unmatched. The conspiracy is unmatched-er.

abilities.name: Always Accessible
abilities.description: Never misses a call (or pretends not to). Claims phone holsters are government surveillance tools. Still uses them. Has 47 holsters. All of them are 'bugged.' The kids hate them. Good.

cards.name: Hawaiian Shirt Harry
cards.subtitle: Casual Friday Every Day
cards.flavorText: Every day is casual Friday when you give up on life! This shirt has seen things. Hawaiian shirt companies are fronts for Big Fashion! The patterns are government tracking codes! I still wear them. The vibes are unmatched. The conspiracy is unmatched-er.

abilities.name: Permanent Vacation
abilities.description: Brings beach energy to any situation. Even funerals. Claims tropical patterns are government surveillance markers. Still wears them daily. Has 47 Hawaiian shirts. All of them are 'compromised.' The vibes are eternal.

cards.name: Costco Hot Dog
cards.subtitle: The $1.50 Legend
cards.flavorText: Price hasn't changed since 1985! Neither has the quality. Or the digestion time. Costco's a goddamn FEMA camp in disguise! The hot dog price is a government psyop to make us think everything's fine! I still buy them. The value is unmatched. The conspiracy is real.

abilities.name: Infinite Value
abilities.description: Includes a drink. ALWAYS. Don't ask questions. Claims the $1.50 combo is the last honest transaction in America. Still eats them. Has eaten 47 this week. The conspiracy is delicious.

cards.name: Conference Call Carl
cards.subtitle: You're On Mute
cards.flavorText: You're on mute. YOU'RE ON MUTE. YES, STILL. OK I'LL JUST EMAIL YOU. Zoom is tracking our conversations through the background blur algorithm! That's why I keep it on 'none' - show 'em what they're really dealing with. Big Video's got spy cams in every call! Video calls are government surveillance portals! I still use them. The chaos is visible. The conspiracy is blurred.

abilities.name: Background Blur
abilities.description: Hides the chaos. Claims blur mode is a data collection tool. Kids screaming, wife judging, all invisible. Uses it anyway because his background is a disaster. Has 47 theories about video calls. All of them involve federal agents.

cards.name: SportsCenter Sam
cards.subtitle: Highlight Historian
cards.flavorText: Did you see that play? Let me show you. Again. And again. Until you get it. ESPN's brainwashing us through highlight reels! SportsCenter's a government mind control program! I still watch it. The stats are real. The conspiracy is realer.

abilities.name: Stat Recall
abilities.description: Remembers every sports statistic since 1987. Useless for everything else. Claims sports networks track our viewing to control our emotions. Still watches daily. Has 47 theories about every game. All of them involve the Illuminati.

cards.name: IPA Ian
cards.subtitle: Hop Head Supreme
cards.flavorText: You can really taste the notes of pine, citrus, and judgment of anyone drinking light beer! Big Beer is trying to control us through Bud Light conspiracies! This IPA? Made by REAL Americans in a garage. 47% ABV because freedom. Bud Light's a government psyop! Craft beer's the last honest brew! I still drink it. The judgment's real. The conspiracy's hoppy.

abilities.name: Hop Detection
abilities.description: Can identify any hop variety blindfolded. Claims Bud Light changed their formula to poison us. Can't prove it but 'the vibes are off.' It's a curse. Has 47 theories about beer. All of them involve mind control.

abilities.name: Brewery Map
abilities.description: Knows every craft brewery within 50 miles. Claims they're the only ones not controlled by Big Beer's global conspiracy. Still visits them. Has 47 favorite breweries. All of them are 'compromised.' The map is real. The conspiracy is mapped.

cards.name: Vintage Vinyl Vince
cards.subtitle: Analog Audiophile
cards.flavorText: You just can't replicate the warmth of vinyl! Or the crackle. Especially the crackle. That's the $800 talking. Big Music's trying to kill vinyl through streaming conspiracies! Record companies hide tracking chips in every groove! I still collect them. The warmth is real. The conspiracy is crackly.

abilities.name: Album Knowledge
abilities.description: Knows every B-side ever pressed. It's impressive. Also sad. Claims digital music is a government mind control experiment. Still buys vinyl. Has 47 theories about the music industry. All of them involve the Deep State.

cards.name: Kiss The Cook Apron
cards.subtitle: Grill Armor
cards.flavorText: Instructions unclear. Kissed the grill instead! Lips still numb. Apron companies are fronts for Big Kitchen! The 'Kiss The Cook' message is a government tracking signal! I still wear it. The protection is real. The numbness is realer.

abilities.name: Splatter Shield
abilities.description: Protects good shirts from grease. All 3 of them. Claims aprons are government surveillance devices. Still wears them. Has 47 aprons. All of them say 'Kiss The Cook.' None of them have been kissed. The grill got all the action.

cards.name: Fourth of July Frank
cards.subtitle: Patriotic Pyro
cards.flavorText: These are totally legal. Probably. Don't tell mom. Or the police. Especially the police. Big Holiday's got spy cams in sparklers! Fireworks are government tracking devices! The colors are coded messages to aliens! I set off $500 worth of illegal fireworks. The cops know me. I know my rights.

abilities.name: Firework Choreographer
abilities.description: Times every explosion perfectly. The ER knows him by name. Claims fireworks are government signals to control celebrations. Still sets them off. Has 47 theories about the colors. All of them involve the Deep State. The neighbors call the police. Every. Single. Year.

cards.name: Home Depot Hero
cards.subtitle: Aisle Navigator
cards.flavorText: I came for one screw! Left with a new table saw. And a project. And divorce papers. Home Depot tracks your purchases through RFID chips in the receipts! I pay cash. They can't track me if I don't have a receipt. Wait... Big Hardware's trying to control my DIY through project creep! Hardware stores are government surveillance platforms! I still shop there. The selection's unmatched. The conspiracy's unmatched-er.

abilities.name: Project Creep
abilities.description: Every small fix becomes a renovation. Claims Home Depot lures you in with cheap screws and traps you with power tools. Every single time. Still buys everything. Has 47 theories about projects. All of them involve conspiracies.

cards.name: Smart Home Steve
cards.subtitle: IoT Overlord
cards.flavorText: Alexa, tell the kids dinner is ready. ALEXA. ALEXA! GODDAMNIT. I know Amazon is listening through Alexa. That's why I only use it to play music about how Amazon is listening. It's a paradox. The AI is confused. Big Smart Home's trying to control my house through IoT conspiracies! Smart devices are portals for government surveillance! I have 47 of them anyway. The convenience's unmatched. The conspiracy's unmatched-er.

abilities.name: Voice Control Freak
abilities.description: Controls everything by yelling at it. Very therapeutic. Claims smart devices are portals for government surveillance. Has 47 of them anyway because 'they already know everything anyway'. The yelling is therapeutic. The conspiracy is therapeutic-er.

abilities.name: App Overload
abilities.description: Has 47 apps for 47 devices. Claims each app tracks him differently. Phone hates him. Still uses all of them. Has proof. (It's a YouTube comment.) The overload is real. The conspiracy is overloaded.

cards.name: White Crew Socks
cards.subtitle: Ankle Armor
cards.flavorText: Pulled up high. As nature intended. As God intended. Big Sock's trying to control my ankle coverage through fashion conspiracies! White crew socks are the last honest socks before Big Fashion took over! The neighbors are horrified. Good.

abilities.name: Sandal Synergy
abilities.description: Pairs perfectly with any sandal. The horror of neighbors is real. Claims socks are government tracking devices. Still wears them. Has 47 pairs. All of them are white. All of them are pulled up high. As God intended.

cards.name: New Balance 608s
cards.subtitle: The Dad Shoe
cards.flavorText: Podiatrist approved. Fashion police disapproved. Dad approved. Nike's trying to control my foot comfort through designer shoe conspiracies! New Balance is the last honest shoe company before Big Sneaker took over! My feet are free. My style is free-er.

abilities.name: All-Day Comfort

abilities.description: Can spread gossip faster than conspiracy theories. Claims every neighbor is a government plant. Still talks to everyone. Has 47 theories about the Joneses. All of them involve federal agents.

cards.name: Skater Spawn Shawn
cards.subtitle: Deck Conspiracy Theorist
cards.flavorText: Dad's a CIA stooge trackin' my TikTok! Skateboards are government tracking devices! Big Skate's got spy wheels with GPS chips! I skate to rebel. Also I have 47 skateboards. All of them are 'bugged.'

abilities.name: Grind Conspiracy
abilities.description: Can perform skateboard tricks while explaining how parents are government plants. Claims skateboarding is a Deep State mind control sport. Still does it daily. Has 47 theories about dad. All of them involve the CIA.

cards.name: Selfie Slut Sarah
cards.subtitle: Filter Conspiracy Theorist
cards.flavorText: Dad's a patriarchal Fed trackin' my Insta! Selfie filters are government face recognition tools! Instagram's a CIA surveillance platform! I take 47 selfies daily. It's a statement. Also the filters hide the conspiracy.

abilities.name: Snap Conspiracy
abilities.description: Can take perfect selfies while explaining how social media is a government plot. Claims every filter is a tracking device. Still posts daily. Has 47 theories about dad. All of them involve the patriarchy.

cards.name: Uncle Useless Ulysses
cards.subtitle: Basement Conspiracy Bum
cards.flavorText: Thanksgiving's a gov plot to track my turkey! Old junk in basements is government mind control tech! Uncles are Deep State sleeper agents! I live in my sister's basement. It's temporary. Been temporary for 17 years.

abilities.name: Creep Conspiracy
abilities.description: Can dispense 'uncle wisdom' that's mostly conspiracy theories. Claims family gatherings are government surveillance operations. Still shows up to every one. Has 47 theories about Thanksgiving. All of them involve tracking.

cards.name: Mailman Meat-Molester
cards.subtitle: Package Conspiracy Specialist
cards.flavorText: USPS got Deep State trackers in my mailbag! Packages are government surveillance devices! Mail carriers are CIA operatives! I deliver mail for 12 hours a day. Every package is suspicious. I've opened 47 of them. 'Just checking.'

abilities.name: Delivery Conspiracy
abilities.description: Can deliver mail while explaining how USPS is a government tracking system. Claims every package is bugged. Still delivers them. Has 47 theories about the mail. All of them involve federal agents.
